docker ps: shows all running containers

docker pull <image-name>: pulls an image (ex: mongo, python, etc.)

docker run -d <image-name>: (creates and) runs a detached image (-d) (so you can use the current terminal)

docker images: displays all downloaded images

docker stop <container-name>: stops a running container

docker rm <container-name>: deletes a container

docker rmi <image-name>: deletes an image

docker build . -t <name>: creates a new image from the current folder with specified name (-t)

docker run -it <image-name>: interactively run an image

sudo docker tag <image-id> <docker-id>/<image-name/:<tag-name> : image tagging


